FBIS4-38080 "drnes124_p_94002" FBIS-NES-94-124 Daily Report 26 Jun 1994 SOUTH ASIA Afghanistan Government Seen Making Progress Against Militia Government Seen Making Progress Against Militia Dostam Aircraft Bomb Herat LD2606171794 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Pashto 1530 GMT 26 Jun 94 LD2606171794 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network Pashto BFN [Text] Approximately 100 people were killed or injured yesterday during an air attack against Herat city. A Bakhtar Information Agency correspondent reports from Herat city that two jets belonging to Dostam's militia bombed the crowded parts of Herat city yesterday. As a result, eight civilians were killed and around 90 people--including women and children--were injured. The report adds that this savage attack occurred on the eve of a meeting of the country's governors in Herat and was an attempt to undermine this meeting. It was reported that the meeting is scheduled to be held in two days--on 28 June. In addition to the country's governors, a number of social and scientific personalities from in and out of Afghanistan will attend it. It is expected that a number of leaders of the jihadi groups will also participate.
